Modifications in this fork
(OtoDock — https://github.com/OtoDock/google-maps-mcp-server):

  * Places `search_places`: reimplemented on the Places API Text Search
    (`googlemaps.Client.places`) to fix multi-word keyword matching. Upstream
    used Nearby Search plus a client-side substring filter, which dropped valid
    multi-word matches (e.g. "gas station"). `get_place_details` was moved onto
    the same `googlemaps` client. This removes the `google-maps-places` (gapic)
    dependency.

  * OtoDock relay support: when `OTODOCK_RELAY_BASE` + `OTODOCK_RELAY_TOKEN` are
    set (hosted mode), all Google Maps calls route through the OtoDock relay —
    which holds the API key, meters usage, and proxies to Google — via a custom
    base URL plus an `X-OtoDock-Relay-Token` header. Otherwise the configured
    `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` is used directly (bring-your-own-key), unchanged.

